bug.short_desc: KDE Plasma user manager is empty
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1224391 user_manager screen
Description of problem: In KDE, users are not listed in the user manager application and thus cannot be edited.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora KDE spin (24 or 25) 2. Open user manager.
Actual results: No users are listed
Expected results: Existing users should be listed

I cannot reproduce on my box.
I recommend you report this upstream @ bugs.kde.org
dnf install accountsservice-libs fix this on my macchine
dnf install accountsservice-libs fixes this for me too, so this report can be closed
